item_prototype.name: psModulePorts for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The port/ring/axis total number ports of the module

item_prototype.name: psModuleType for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The module function type

item_prototype.name: psState for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The PCI device enable status

item_prototype.name: psIRQ for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: which interrupt pin the device uses.

item_prototype.name: psLength for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The length of each PCI resource. It will be encoded as hex. For example: Length 0x20000 will be encoded as (hex) 00 00 00 00 00 02 00 00

item_prototype.name: psBaseAddress for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: Base address mapping registers for memory and IO. Refer to the PCI specification for the format. A memory or IO address is encoded as hex. For example: A memory start address 0xF7E00000 will be encoded as (hex)00 00 00 00 F7 E0 00 00. According to the PCI specification, The IO address bit 0 will be 1. An IO address 0xE800 will be encoded as (hex)00 00 00 00 00 00 E8 01.

item_prototype.name: psLocation for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The location information consists of PCI bus number, device number, and function. e.g. PCI bus 0, device 0, funciton 0

item_prototype.name: psManufacturer for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The manufacturer name of the PCI device

item_prototype.name: psClassCode for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: Identifies the generic function of the device. Base Sub- Prog Class Class If. Description ------ ------ ------ -------------------------------------- 00h Device was built before Class Code definitions were finalized

item_prototype.name: psSubsysDeviceID for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: Identifies the particular device subsystem. This identier is allocated by the vendor. Subsystem Device ID Description ------------------- -------------------------------------- 4097(0x1001) NVRAM with KW 4113(0x1011) NVRAM without KW

item_prototype.name: psSubsysVendorID for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: Identifies the manufacturer subsystem of the device. 65535(0xFFFF) is an invalid value for a vendor ID. Subsys Vendor ID Manufacturer ---------------- ------------ 5118(0x13FE) Advantech Co.

item.name: sysBootCount
item.description: The boot count since the entity/device was first boot.

item.name: sysBootTime
item.description: The time since the entity/device was last re-initialized. A date-time specification. field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 8 9 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 10 hours from UTC 0..11 10 11 minutes from UTC 0..59 If this information is not known, then this variable shall have the value corresponding to January 1, year 0000, 00:00:00.0, which is encoded as (hex)'00 00 01 01 00 00 00 00'.

item.name: sysFirstBootTime
item.description: The first boot time since the entity/device was started it will be reset if the device cleaned all files and registry with clean boot. A date-time specification. field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 8 9 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 10 hours from UTC 0..11 10 11 minutes from UTC 0..59 If this information is not known, then this variable shall have the value corresponding to January 1, year 0000, 00:00:00.0, which is encoded as (hex)'00 00 01 01 00 00 00 00'.

item.name: sysReleaseDate
item.description: The release date of the entity/device.

item.name: sysImageVersion
item.description: The release version number of the entity/device.

item.name: sysDescr
item.description: A textual description of the entity/device that this only contain printable ASCII characters.

item.name: sysDeviceName
item.description: The user defined name of the device, e.g. alias name, may be its device location.

item.name: sysModuleID
item.description: The module name of the device. This value should include the full name of the hardware. It is mandatory that this only contain printable ASCII characters. e.g. UNO-2184G, TPC-1840WP. etc,.
